outcome_space.description: US Real GDP Quarter-over-Quarter Annualized Growth Rate (Advance Estimate)

base_case.condition: What will the US GDP Quarterly Advanced Estimate annualized growth rate be at {observation.reference_date}?
base_case.fsp_resolution: FSP equals the seasonally adjusted annual rate of real GDP growth for the Quarter beginning {observation.reference_date} as reported by the U.S. Bureau of Economic Analysis (BEA) in their Gross Domestic Product (Advance Estimate) news release on {observation.release_date}. This is the quarter-over-quarter change expressed as an annualized rate. The Advance Estimate is published three times to release, update and finalize; this product settles against the first official release of {observation.release_date}.

edge_cases.condition: BEA does not publish a finalized US GDP Quarterly (Advance Estimate) for the quarter by 138 days after the first release on {observation.release_date}. (138 days being the sum of 48 days between first release and finalized release of the Advance Estimate, and an additional 90 days.)
